VIMS PROJECT
VIMS: Vendor & Invoice Management System
Project Status: Core Engine Complete 🚀
1. System Overview
VIMS is a specialized "Line-Item" billing application designed to track individual service orders performed by various Vendors for specific Customers. Unlike standard invoicing, every task is stored as a unique entity with a custom alphanumeric ID before being grouped into a final bill.

2. The Data Architecture (Schema)
The system runs on Node.js/Express with a SQLite database managed via Sequelize.

Vendors: Master records of service providers.

Customers: Master records of clients to be billed.

Services (The "Work Order"): * Linked to: 1 Vendor AND 1 Customer.

Unique ID Format: WXXXX (starts at W0001, auto-scales to W10000+).

Fields: Description, Hours, Rate, Total (Hours * Rate), Status (pending or invoiced).

Invoices: Master billing records that group multiple pending services into a single total.

3. Current Key Features
Sequential Work Orders: Every service is automatically assigned the next available W-Code.

Safety Deletion: Services can be removed via a "Delete" button that requires a browser-native confirmation (window.confirm) to prevent data loss.

Relational Integrity: Services cannot exist without a valid Vendor and Customer.

Dynamic Grouping: The system identifies all "Pending" work for a selected customer and "locks" them into a new Invoice record.

4. Technical Configuration
Backend Port: 5000

Frontend Port: 3000 (React default)

Database Sync Policy: force: false (to preserve data). Note: Use force: true only if changing the model structure.

5. Development Roadmap (Next Steps)
When resuming, the following features are prioritized:

Vendor Payout Reports: A table summarizing total "Pending" dollars owed to each specific Vendor.

Search & Filter: The ability to search the History table by W-Code or filter by Vendor name.

PDF Export: Generating a professional-grade invoice document for the Customer.

Edit Mode: The ability to adjust hours or rates on an existing Work Order before it is invoiced.
